      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thy name shall be called no more Jacob, but Israel; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that is, not only ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jacob, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Israel, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or Israel preferably to Jacob. Moses might truly say, God made this covenant with them then present before him; for a great part of them, even all who were under twenty years of age, when God gave the law on mount Sinai, were at Horeb; and, as God foreknew that their parents would die in the wilderness for their unbelief and murmuring, and would have comparatively little profit from that covenant, he especially intended it for those who should enter Canaan, and who, with their posterity, should be governed and benefited by it from generation to generation.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
